  "chart": {
    "$description": "Harmonized canonical values — tuning/plots.js, artifacts/gallery.js and lattice_dashboard/dashboard.js each hand-rolled distinct paper/plot/grid/axis colors (tuning: #0a0f1a flat; artifacts: #131c2e/#0b1120 two-tone; lattice: transparent/rgba(22,26,36,.95)). Canonical choice: paper-bg = plot-bg = bg.primary (tuning's flat single-background convention, closest to hub/app-shell values); axis-text/grid = text.secondary family at low alpha (tuning AND artifacts dark both already used #8b9ab5 for axis-text — the one point of agreement). Artifacts and lattice will visually shift when migrated (Task 3.1/3.6) — authorized minor-shade harmonization, not a redesign.",
    "paper-bg": { "$value": "{color.slate.1000}", "$type": "color" },
    "plot-bg": { "$value": "{color.slate.1000}", "$type": "color" },
    "grid": { "$value": "rgba(139, 154, 181, 0.1)", "$type": "color", "$description": "text.secondary base (#8b9ab5) at 10% alpha — tuning's exact dark-mode grid value." },
    "axis-text": { "$value": "{color.slate.600}", "$type": "color" },
    "series": {
      "$description": "Canonical 6-slot categorical palette = tuning's COLORS.bo_palette verbatim (all 6 steps already existed as ramp aliases). Artifacts' own 8-color array (which adds #d4a574 and an unratified pink #e879f9 not in any of the 7 approved ramp families) is NOT carried forward; artifacts' migration (Task 3.1, out of this task's scope) maps down to these 6 slots.",
